it doesn't inherit when importing the BOM. I need to clarify this to ensure all dependencies are correctly managed.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring artifact dependencies**\\n\\nIt seems the artifact isn't standalone, as normal documentation suggests adding both the generator and the module. The current build does include both. However, if the scaffold only targets the library without explicitly providing a generator dependency, tests might fail to compile or use the SchemaGenerator. I'm questioning whether the generator should be included deterministically to ensure everything works properly. Let's think this through to determine the best approach!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_iRd4Z8mp6JNhj40RE2t9620q|fc_056e1d7653677390016a40571c7aa48195be435e5b9bfff54b", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "/home/vjovanov/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/com.github.victools/jsonschema-generator/4.38.0/21f7941502b59b369a2e975cfd6e2459faf098f0/jsonschema-generator-4.38.0.pom", "limit": 80}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 4678, "output": 1451, "cacheRead": 25088, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31217, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782601482112, "responseId": "resp_056e1d7653677390016a40570aa2e0819588c28d63233d00db"}}
